2011-04-06T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/makora-open-finance-polski-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 1.5 percent. The Czech PX Index
added 0.9 percent. Hungary’s BUX Index gained 3.2 percent.  Makora Krosnienska Huta Szkla SA (MRA PW): The Polish glass
manufacturer will start trading on Newconnect, the  Warsaw Stock
Exchange ’s market for smaller companies.  Open Finance SA (OPF PW): The financial-services broker
controlled by Polish billionaire Leszek Czarnecki said that BZ
WBK AIB Asset Management SA increased its stake in Open Finance
to 5.4 percent. The shares gained 0.1 percent to 18.42 zloty.  Polski Fundusz Hipoteczny SA (PFH PW): The Polish mortgage
debt collecting company is set to debut on Newconnect.  To contact the reporters on this story:
